    "For instance, claim decomposition may result in over-specification where the claim is decomposed to minute granularity or under-specification where the claim is not decomposed sufficiently.",
    "An example of over-specification is shown in the first example for Program-FC in Table 11 where the claim is over decomposed leading to an erroneous prediction.",
    "The second example demonstrates a case of under-specification where the claim is not decomposed, leading to limited information and erroneous verdict.",
    "We introduce QuanTemp, the largest real-world fact-checking dataset to date, featuring numerical data from global fact-checking sites.",
